Why it fits: The recommendation aligns with your taste for classic adventure/fantasy with mythic elements (closest match: The Hobbit). If you enjoy mythic worldbuilding and episodic adventure that blends childlike wonder with deeper themes, this is a good fit.

5) The Picture of Dorian Gray — Oscar Wilde (1998 edition)  
Short description: A philosophical novel about beauty, moral corruption, and the consequences of living for sensation and appearance.  
Why it fits: The tool connected this to the thought-provoking, morally-questioning works already in your profile (closest match: Brave New World). If you like novels that combine stylish prose with ethical and social critique, Wilde’s tale should resonate.

